V'''Phillip H. Wiebe''' (born 1945) is the former Chair of the Department of Philosophy, Professor of Philosophy and former Dean of Arts and Religious Studies at [[Trinity Western University]] and its School of Graduate Studies. He is the author of ''God and Other Spirits'' and ''Visions of Jesus,'' both from [[Oxford University Press]]. His primary areas of research are in philosophy of religion and science, and epistemology.\u000a\u000a==Degrees==\u000aHe received a B.A. and  M.A.. from the [[University of Manitoba]], and a  Ph.D. from the [[University of Adelaide]].\u000a*Studied at Adelaide under notable scholar [[J.J.C. Smart|J. J. C. Smart]],  .\u000a\u000a==Areas of expertise==\u000aAnalytic philosophy; philosophy of religion, religious experience. \u000a*Some have described Phillip Wiebe as a "Mystical Empiricist." \u000a*Also a noted [[Shroud of Turin]] expert.\u000a  \u000a==Works==\u000a===Books===\u000a*{{cite book |author1-last=Wiebe |author1-first=Phillip H. |title=Theism in an Age of Science |location=Lanham, MD |publisher=American University Press |date=1988 |isbn=978-0-819-16820-7 |oclc=17202715 }}\u000a*{{cite book |author1-last=Wiebe |author1-first=Phillip H. |author1-mask=3 |title=Visions of Jesus: direct encounters from the New Testament to today |location=New York ; Oxford |publisher=[[Oxford University Press]] |date=1997 |isbn=978-0-195-09750-4 |oclc=35884871 }}<ref>{{cite web|title=Library Journal Review|url=http://www.syndetics.com/index.aspx?client&isbn=0195097505%2fLJREVIEW.HTML&type=hw5&newwin=yes|accessdate=May 10, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Summary|url=http://www.syndetics.com/index.aspx?client&isbn=0195097505%2fSUMMARY.HTML&type=hw5&newwin=yes|accessdate=May 10, 2016}}</ref>\u000a*{{cite book |author1-last=Wiebe |author1-first=Phillip H. |author1-mask=3 |title=God and Other Spirits: intimations of transcendence in Christian experience |location=New York ; Oxford |publisher=Oxford University Press |date=2004 |isbn=978-0-195-14012-5 |oclc=52091936 }}<ref>{{cite web|title=Table of contents|url=http://www.loc.gov/catdir/toc/ecip042/2003008299.html|accessdate=May 10, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Summary|url=http://www.syndetics.com/index.aspx?client&isbn=0195140125%2fSUMMARY.HTML&type=hw5&newwin=yes|accessdate=May 10, 2016}}</ref> According to [[WorldCat]], the book is held in 698 libraries <ref>{{cite web|title=WorldCat book entry|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/god-and-other-spirits-intimations-of-transcendence-in-christian-experience/oclc/61329690&referer=brief_results|accessdate=May 10, 2016}}</ref>\u000a*{{cite book |author1-last=Wiebe |author1-first=Phillip H. |author1-mask=3 |title=Visions and appearances of Jesus |location=Abilene, TX |publisher=Leafwood Publishers |date=2014 |isbn=978-0-891-12608-9 |oclc=868642309 }}\u000a*{{cite book |author1-last=Wiebe |author1-first=Phillip H. |author1-mask=3 |title=Intuitive knowing as spiritual experience |location=New York, NY |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |date=2015 |isbn=978-1-137-54948-8 |oclc=907621832 }}\u000a\u000a==References==\u000a{{Reflist}}\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Wiebe, Phillip H}}\u000a[[Category:20th-century philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:21st-century philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Canadian philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Philosophers of religion]]\u000a[[Category:Epistemologists]]\u000a[[Category:Epistemology of religion]]\u000a[[Category:Philosophers of science]]\u000a[[Category:Living people]]\u000a[[Category:Researchers of the Shroud of Turin]]\u000a[[Category:1945 births]]\u000a[[Category:University of Manitoba alumni]]\u000a[[Category:University of Adelaide alumni]]\u000a\u000a\u000a{{Canada-writer-stub}}
